that? [$ (said the Farmer.) $] (^Why truly^)
[$reply'd (^Holloway^) $] (^understanding that you
<P 99>
receiv'd Ten Pounds at the Inn from whence
you now came, for I was drinking in the
next Room when 'twas paid you, Necessity
obliges me to borrow it, therefore if you are
not willing to lend it me by fair Means,
you must by foul Means^) . [$The Farmer
being a Man of some Courage, 
presently drew his Hanger in his own
Defence, but that being no security
against Pistols, which could kill at a 
Distance, (^Holloway^) shot his Horse
under him, so dismounting his
Antagonist, and riding up to him with
another Pistol ready cockt, and 
presenting it to the Farmer's Breast, he lent
him his Money without taking a Note
of his Hand for't.$]

   [$Another time (^Holloway^) meeting with
a Gentleman on the Road, who had
like to have been robb'd but a little
before, he told the said (^Holloway^) , as
